-- Petrobras lawyers working to overturn Brazil ban on Transocean
-- 
-- Thu Sep 20, 2012 6:34pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/20/us-petrobras-transocean-idUSBRE88J1EN20120920

 

 RIO DE JANEIRO  (Reuters) - Brazil's state-led oil company Petrobras ( PETR4.SA ) has its lawyers working to help drilling contractor Transocean ( RIG.N ) overturn a ban in the country related to a November oil spill at an offshore field operated by Chevron Corp ( CVX.N ). 
 Transocean has 10 rigs working in Brazil -- seven of them for Petrobras. (Reporting by Jeb Blount; Writing by Brad Haynes)